1
00:01:49,020 --> 00:01:53,520
One day, in the forest

2
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:58,520
I met a bear

3
00:01:58,520 --> 00:02:03,520
On the forest path where flowers bloom

4
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:08,520
I met a bear

5
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:13,520
The bear said,

6
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:18,520
"Miss, you better run away."

7
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:20,520
Scat, scat!

8
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:24,760
Oh!

9
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:26,740
Thank you.

10
00:02:26,740 --> 00:02:36,600
This time capsule will be opened
in 2025, our school's 50th anniversary year.

11
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:40,520
It’s the year everyone turns 34.

12
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,760
Thirty-four!

13
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:47,620
I wonder what kind of adults
you’ll all be by then.

14
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:07,620
“In Celebration of the 50th Anniversary.
Invitation to the Time Capsule Event.”

15
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:19,020
Ah!

16
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:26,840
This is a non-smoking area.

17
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,520
Yes.

18
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:31,020
What about saying sorry?

19
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:34,000
I'm sorry.

20
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:39,640
Hey you! You, you...!

21
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:42,900
- Kanon, breakfast’s ready.
- Mom, Dad was…

22
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:45,720
- Breakfast’s ready!
- Stop it!

23
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:49,520
- Hey, it’s gonna get cold…
- Okay.

24
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:54,020
Sorry.

25
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,520
Alright, let’s eat!

26
00:03:58,580 --> 00:04:00,020
Yes?

27
00:04:00,020 --> 00:04:02,200
Excuse me.

28
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:05,520
- King!
- Hin?

29
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:07,560
- Long time no see!
- Wow!

30
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:10,520
- You haven’t changed at all.
- Wait, what’s going on?

31
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:13,640
I came to pick you up, King.

32
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,020
King?

33
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:19,200
- Your daughter?
- Yeah.

34
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:23,740
Your dad’s nickname was
"King" back in elementary school.

35
00:04:23,740 --> 00:04:24,840
Wow.

36
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:29,960
He was always late. I was the one
who had to pick him up all the time.

37
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:31,860
- Hey, cut it out.
- It’s fine.

38
00:04:31,860 --> 00:04:34,520
- Sorry for bothering you.
- No, not at all.

39
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:36,520
It’s not fun without him.

40
00:04:36,520 --> 00:04:39,020
What are you going to do with Dad?

41
00:04:39,020 --> 00:04:42,520
We're digging up the time capsule.

42
00:04:42,620 --> 00:04:46,520
“50th Anniversary”

43
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:50,180
We’re happy to see
you became the principal.

44
00:04:50,180 --> 00:04:53,020
I'm just being used
for their convenience.

45
00:04:53,020 --> 00:04:56,520
But I’m retiring this year, so
one last service for the school.

46
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:58,520
King!

47
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:01,520
- Long time no see!
- Toyo, long time no see!

48
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:04,340
King! Really, you haven’t changed!

49
00:05:04,340 --> 00:05:06,800
- Yukki! Long time no see.
- Long time.

50
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,620
Hey, what about me?

51
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:11,760
Hin? Don’t you look kinda shady?

52
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:14,020
It’s true.
Did you start wearing glasses?

53
00:05:14,020 --> 00:05:16,520
- No, I’ve worn them!
- Maybe you didn’t?

54
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:19,620
- What’s that about!
- Yo!

55
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:21,800
- Kantaro!
- Long time no see!

56
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:24,520
- You’ve gotten big.
- I’ve been eating too much.

57
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:28,520
Those who haven't registered yet,
please check in.

58
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:31,140
Iinchou.
That feeling’s so nostalgic.

59
00:05:31,140 --> 00:05:33,020
Ms. Kobayashi.

60
00:05:33,020 --> 00:05:37,940
Sorry, can you return the supplies
to the guardroom whem you’re done?

61
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:39,720
Aren’t you coming?

62
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:43,900
It’s better if the teacher isn’t
around at times like this,.

63
00:05:43,900 --> 00:05:46,520
- Please take care of things.
- Okay.

64
00:05:49,020 --> 00:05:53,020
Huh?
The important star isn’t here.

65
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:56,340
- I heard Tabo’s overseas.
- No, not that...

66
00:05:56,340 --> 00:05:58,520
Who have you been looking for?

67
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:01,520
Obviously, it’s Sonoko Saruhashi.

68
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:04,160
The too-beautiful reporter, huh?

69
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:07,300
I bought the magazine
with her interview.

70
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:09,120
Hin, you’re such a fanboy!

71
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:12,520
Isn’t it lucky to have a
celebrity in our class?

72
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:15,020
And she’s single too.

73
00:06:15,020 --> 00:06:16,800
Think there’s a chance?

74
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:21,020
No way!
But yeah, she really is amazing.

75
00:06:21,020 --> 00:06:24,260
She was even on TV
as a commentator.

76
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:30,160
Still, such a busy celebrity wouldn’t
bother coming to a class reunion.

77
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:57,400
Um... Hi…

78
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,520
From 6th grade, class 1...?

79
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:05,520
Huh... was I wrong?

80
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:10,760
No, you’re right!

81
00:07:11,820 --> 00:07:16,020
We’ve been waiting for you!
Sonoko Saruhashi!

82
00:07:16,020 --> 00:07:18,880
Do you remember me?
I’m Takeda.

83
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:20,940
Everyone used to call me “Hin.”

84
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:25,720
- Ah, Hin! I remember you.
- Really? No way, yay!

85
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:28,020
W-w-what about me?
I’m Sakurai!

86
00:07:28,020 --> 00:07:30,020
Actually, my name’s Kanta. But…

87
00:07:30,020 --> 00:07:32,520
Hey, everyone,
this is way too sudden.

88
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:37,300
- Sorry about that.
- No, Iinchou, you haven’t changed.

89
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:40,200
- You remember me?
- Of course.

90
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:43,280
Ah... thank you so much.

91
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:47,140
Come on, everyone,
use your hands.

92
00:07:47,140 --> 00:07:50,020
- Okay, let's start, hurry up.
- Okay.

93
00:08:00,020 --> 00:08:02,020
Looks like we found it.

94
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:06,020
Oh! Hey everyone,
we found it. Gather up!

95
00:08:11,020 --> 00:08:14,520
Oh!

96
00:08:19,020 --> 00:08:21,020
- Alright, here we go.
- Okay.

97
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:25,380
Oh.

98
00:08:25,380 --> 00:08:28,020
"Everyone's Dreams"?

99
00:08:29,220 --> 00:08:31,520
I'll put it down here for now.

100
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:52,680
Wow, this brings back memories!

101
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:55,200
My dream was to be a firefighter.

102
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:59,300
I had dreams like this…
It came true!

103
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:02,020
I totally forgot about this.

104
00:09:02,020 --> 00:09:04,940
No, it did come true!

105
00:09:04,940 --> 00:09:06,500
Hin, what’s this?

106
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:10,520
Ah, this? This is "Flying in the Sky."

107
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:15,020
I hope that dream comes true.

108
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:19,280
Takaki, what did you draw?

109
00:09:19,280 --> 00:09:21,740
Well... something...
just whatever?

110
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:24,020
It’s the yearbook!

111
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,520
Whoa!

112
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:57,520
What the heck... is this?
Who messed with my photo?

113
00:09:57,520 --> 00:10:01,240
No... me too... you know?

114
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:04,520
I mean... isn’t this kinda creepy?

115
00:10:40,980 --> 00:10:45,280
THE RIGHT TO JUDGE

116
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:03,520
So, who the hell
did this prank?

117
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:05,700
Maybe someone’s
holding a grudge?

118
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:08,120
Huh? I have no idea.

119
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:10,440
But those six were close friends.

120
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:13,700
- You were always together, right?
- Yeah, that’s true.

121
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:18,400
Me, King, Kantaro, and then Tabo...

122
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:22,320
No need to worry about it.
It’s just a childhood prank, right?

123
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:26,260
Never mind that, try our
famous grilled chicken.

124
00:12:26,260 --> 00:12:29,840
Wow, that looks super delicious!

125
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:33,200
- Thanks for the meal, manager!
- No problem.

126
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:35,020
Thank you!

127
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:40,100
What do we do with the drawings
from those absent today?

128
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:45,020
Right, some people, we don’t even know
where they live to send it to.

129
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:51,340
Hey everyone,
can I have your attention?

130
00:12:51,340 --> 00:12:54,260
Anyone keeping in touch with
people not here?

131
00:12:54,260 --> 00:12:57,020
We need to hand over
the drawings, you know.

132
00:12:57,020 --> 00:12:58,520
Ah.

133
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:04,020
Since I left for school, I haven’t
come back at all, so I don’t know.

134
00:13:04,020 --> 00:13:08,900
I used to meet them around New Year,
but the kids have grown up so…

135
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:11,340
Yukki, how old is Yamato now?

136
00:13:11,340 --> 00:13:13,020
He’s 13.

137
00:13:13,020 --> 00:13:15,600
- Thirteen!
- Middle school?!

138
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:19,700
- Why don’t you hold on to it, King?
- Huh? Why me?

139
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:24,020
You’re still living at your family home.
Everyone can pick it up, right?

140
00:13:24,020 --> 00:13:25,780
Don’t just say whatever.

141
00:13:25,780 --> 00:13:28,020
- What?
- I’m counting on you.

142
00:13:28,020 --> 00:13:30,020
- Where are you going?
- Hey, where are you going?

143
00:13:30,020 --> 00:13:31,520
Hin!

144
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:34,720
Hey, Hin!

145
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:37,820
Alright, excuse me for a moment.

146
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:41,020
That guy...

147
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:44,520
Doesn’t look it, he’s a
hospital pharmacist.

148
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:45,860
Oh, really?

149
00:13:45,860 --> 00:13:49,360
- You took over the family business, right?
- Yeah, pretty much.

150
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,520
So you’re the president of
Takaki Painting.

151
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:55,020
You’re exaggerating.
It's just a small paint shop.

152
00:13:55,020 --> 00:13:58,520
But you’re married and have a kid,
that’s impressive.

153
00:13:58,520 --> 00:14:02,260
- Not really.
- Well done. Be proud of yourself.

154
00:14:02,260 --> 00:14:05,060
What’s that supposed to mean...!

155
00:14:06,020 --> 00:14:09,520
Is it true, Saruhashi,
that you’re single?

156
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:28,760
Iinchou, you smoke?

157
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:32,520
An honor student…
and now a bad girl, huh?

158
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:34,600
It’s not like that.

159
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:37,520
Everyone changes.

160
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:40,960
It’d be weird if we didn’t
change after 22 years.

161
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:44,520
Yeah, that’s true.

162
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:50,420
Ah, thanks for organizing everything.

163
00:14:50,420 --> 00:14:53,520
Oh, no problem at all.

164
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:59,020
- You’re the leader, right?
- No, I’m not really a leader.

165
00:14:59,020 --> 00:15:01,020
You are.

166
00:15:01,020 --> 00:15:10,020
We always chose your ideas, and
whatever you began quickly caught on.

167
00:15:10,020 --> 00:15:13,020
The class president was just a title.

168
00:15:13,020 --> 00:15:16,520
That’s why you’re the King!

169
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:19,520
King was just a nickname, after all.

170
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:23,020
But everyone admired you
for that kind of thing.

171
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:35,520
Huh?

172
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:38,520
Ah... nevermind.

173
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:54,760
But do reporters usually
show their faces?

174
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:57,960
Well, normally they don’t...

175
00:15:57,960 --> 00:16:01,220
- That was kind of an accident.
- An accident?

176
00:16:01,220 --> 00:16:06,640
The tabloid photo even caught
her face in the window reflection.

177
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:12,000
It went viral online as "too beautiful"
and she became famous overnight.

178
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:14,800
I’ve been showing it off at parties.

179
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:17,520
- Hey!
- What’s so great about that?

180
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:22,020
Sorry, I need to use the restroom.

181
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:26,520
- That was pretty wild, huh?
- Thanks.

182
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:30,020
- It really blew up online...
- Yeah, it was insane.

183
00:16:52,860 --> 00:16:56,520
Hey! That’s Saruhashi’s!
What do you think you’re doing?!

184
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:59,520
- Look at this.
- Huh? Ah...

185
00:17:02,220 --> 00:17:04,020
It’s completely black.

186
00:17:04,020 --> 00:17:07,940
This is her dream, right?

187
00:17:07,940 --> 00:17:10,520
This is a bit...

188
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:20,020
We didn’t see anything.

189
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:25,520
- Is something wrong?
- Ah!

190
00:17:29,340 --> 00:17:31,520
Kantaro, a highball.

191
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:33,520
Ah, me too, me too...

192
00:17:38,220 --> 00:17:41,020
- Made it just in time.
- Good job.

193
00:17:41,020 --> 00:17:44,520
Ah, Saruhashi, there’s still room.

194
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:48,020
I’m fine, I’ll take the stairs.

195
00:17:48,020 --> 00:17:50,020
- Huh?
- Why?

196
00:17:51,660 --> 00:17:54,080
You’re coming to
round two, right, Kantaro?

197
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:56,520
Of course!
I’m the only one sober!

198
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:58,020
Well then, I’ll be going...

199
00:17:58,020 --> 00:18:01,020
- Hey idiot!
- What are we gonna do without you!

200
00:18:01,020 --> 00:18:02,520
Knew you’d say.

201
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:05,020
What about you guys?
Are you coming?

202
00:18:05,020 --> 00:18:08,520
- We’re heading to the city.
- How about you, Iinchou and Yukki?

203
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:11,440
My kid’s waiting at home.

204
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:14,920
Me too, I’m going.
Everyone, don’t get too late.

205
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:17,020
We’re not kids!

206
00:18:19,020 --> 00:18:22,940
- See you.
- See you, again.

207
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:24,520
Ah, good luck, Saruhashi.

208
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:26,520
We’re cheering for you.

209
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:42,020
Here you go, alright.

210
00:18:42,020 --> 00:18:43,800
- That’s a hit, right?
- Yeah, yeah.

211
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:46,020
- That’s how it goes.
- But what about this?

212
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:49,380
Damn...

213
00:18:49,380 --> 00:18:52,160
Welcome...
Oh, it’s just Takaki!

214
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:54,380
What do you mean ‘just’?
I’m a customer.

215
00:18:54,380 --> 00:18:58,380
- Huh? Friends?
- We were classmates.

216
00:18:58,380 --> 00:19:00,520
Oh, this is nice!

217
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:03,520
Thanks!
I’m Imakuni, the owner.

218
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:06,700
Moeka, show them to their seats.

219
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:09,020
This way, please.

220
00:19:10,620 --> 00:19:13,840
- Do you come here often?
- About the last six months or so.

221
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:15,760
Now, it’s almost every day.

222
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:18,520
His wife’s so scary
he doesn’t have a place at home.

223
00:19:18,520 --> 00:19:22,520
You can’t say that, Ucchan, you
come here almost every day too!

224
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:26,220
- Wait, wait...
- Yes!

225
00:19:26,220 --> 00:19:30,020
- Oh! 'HOT LIMIT'!
- Yeah! This is it...

226
00:19:30,020 --> 00:19:33,520
Yo! Say,
summer stirs the heart

227
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:37,600
Bare legs,
the enchanting mermaid…!

228
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:39,520
Ugh, Heisei era…

229
00:19:41,020 --> 00:19:44,020
That was kind of lame,
Sonoko Saruhashi.

230
00:19:44,020 --> 00:19:46,520
- Weren’t you going for?
- Moeka.

231
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:49,260
- Like, 'I’m a celebrity,'
- Moeka…!

232
00:19:49,260 --> 00:19:54,520
'I live in a different world from you guys.'
She was totally giving off that vibe.

233
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:58,280
That dark, gloomy drawing
is kinda creepy, huh.

234
00:19:58,280 --> 00:19:59,520
Huh?

235
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:07,020
Has she always been like that?

236
00:20:07,020 --> 00:20:09,020
I can’t remember that at all.

237
00:20:09,020 --> 00:20:12,800
- She had a nickname, right?
- Ah... yeah, she did.

238
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:15,740
- Huh? What was it? Um…
- What was it?

239
00:20:15,740 --> 00:20:18,520
- Konoko...?
- Huh?

240
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:20,640
- Kinoko?
- Huh?

241
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:23,720
- Something like that.
- Huh? What was it?

242
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:25,920
Donoko.

243
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:27,820
- That’s it.
- That’s it, exactly.

244
00:20:27,820 --> 00:20:30,140
She was often teased with
'That kid? Which kid?'

245
00:20:30,140 --> 00:20:33,020
But that Donoko is
now a popular person.

246
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:35,520
Life’s unpredictable.

247
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:34,760
Please, come on…

248
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:37,140
Ah! Yay!

249
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:03,020
See you at my wedding!

250
00:22:03,020 --> 00:22:05,820
First, get a girlfriend!

251
00:22:05,820 --> 00:22:07,400
- See you, King.
- See ya.

252
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:10,260
- See ya.
- Take care.

253
00:22:10,260 --> 00:22:13,660
- Come have a drink sometime.
- Yeah, I’ll be there.

254
00:22:30,020 --> 00:22:34,520
Meeting and parting in the sky of departure

255
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:39,520
Drawing all the days of youth

256
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:44,520
One day, we’ll each bloom a big flower

257
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:48,020
Blooming beautiful flowers

258
00:22:48,020 --> 00:22:51,520
And laugh together again

259
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:36,560
“Takaki Painting”

260
00:23:42,140 --> 00:23:43,640
Excuse me…

261
00:23:45,140 --> 00:23:46,120
Yes?

262
00:23:47,140 --> 00:23:49,520
Um… May I ask who you are?

263
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:52,780
- I’m Kaneda from the MPD.
- I’m Yoshioka.

264
00:23:52,780 --> 00:23:53,820
Police?

265
00:23:53,820 --> 00:23:57,760
- Are you Sho Takaki?
- Yes.

266
00:23:57,760 --> 00:24:02,580
You were with
Toshiki Takeda last night, right?

267
00:24:02,580 --> 00:24:05,080
Y-Yeah, I was with him.

268
00:24:05,080 --> 00:24:07,080
Huh? What about Hin?

269
00:24:08,300 --> 00:24:10,440
He passed away last night.

270
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,800
What...?

271
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:21,860
Last night, this man fell from
an apartment building and died.

272
00:24:21,860 --> 00:24:22,940
And?

273
00:24:22,940 --> 00:24:25,680
May I cover this for the magazine?

274
00:24:25,680 --> 00:24:28,700
I decide what goes in the magazine.

275
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:31,800
I understand.
I’ll make sure it’s worth publishing.

276
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:37,800
You’re an important part of our team.

277
00:24:37,800 --> 00:24:44,140
There’s no value in using you for a story about
some unknown guy who died from a fall.

278
00:24:44,140 --> 00:24:46,080
I believe it’s something
only I can do.

279
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:47,800
Saruhashi.

280
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:51,800
There must be other jobs
only you can do.

281
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:55,060
Go back to your desk.

282
00:24:55,060 --> 00:24:57,800
Well then,
thank you for your cooperation.

283
00:25:01,780 --> 00:25:03,300
Excuse me…

284
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:08,040
Um…

285
00:25:09,300 --> 00:25:12,320
Is this an incident?

286
00:25:13,420 --> 00:25:17,300
Right now, it doesn’t
look like a serious case.

287
00:25:17,300 --> 00:25:22,300
He seemed pretty drunk,
so it might have been an accident.

288
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:27,300
Or... is there something bothering you?

289
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:32,140
Who messed with my photo?

290
00:25:32,140 --> 00:25:34,740
Maybe someone’s
holding a grudge?

291
00:25:34,740 --> 00:25:37,600
No, nothing like that.

292
00:25:37,600 --> 00:25:41,280
I see. Well then, excuse us.

293
00:25:42,020 --> 00:25:44,760
“Sonoko Saruhashi’s top choice”

294
00:25:48,260 --> 00:25:51,800
- No luck, huh.
- Yeah.

295
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:55,420
With that attitude,
nothing’s gonna move.

296
00:25:57,300 --> 00:26:00,800
Whoa, what’s this...
This is nasty.

297
00:26:02,300 --> 00:26:05,800
The yearbook
found in the time capsule.

298
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:13,800
For some reason, six photos were blacked out,
and one of those people died last night.

299
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:16,300
What’s that?
Sounds kinda interesting.

300
00:26:16,300 --> 00:26:20,540
And that deceased man
was my classmate.

301
00:26:20,540 --> 00:26:22,800
Oh!

302
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:26,800
"Classmate of the too-beautiful reporter,
mysterious suspicious death.

303
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:30,460
Blacked-out album, remaining 5 people,"
something like that?

304
00:26:30,460 --> 00:26:32,720
Yeah, something like that.

305
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:38,800
So, why are these six people's
photos blacked out?

306
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:41,500
Maybe because they’re bad kids…

307
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:43,300
Bad kids?

308
00:26:45,800 --> 00:26:49,120
Yeah... bad kids.

309
00:26:50,060 --> 00:26:55,300
I appreciate your concern,
but you’re overthinking it.

310
00:26:55,300 --> 00:26:56,980
But Hin is...

311
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:00,220
I know it’s tough.

312
00:27:01,300 --> 00:27:04,360
Honestly, my head
can’t keep up either.

313
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:09,620
But that doesn’t mean
he was murdered.

314
00:27:09,620 --> 00:27:13,300
Besides, the police say
an accident is more likely.

315
00:27:15,500 --> 00:27:20,000
Then... what about
that yearbook?

316
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:23,980
- It’s just a prank.
- That might be true, but...

317
00:27:23,980 --> 00:27:28,300
Even if what you say is true,
then why us?

318
00:27:30,300 --> 00:27:32,940
Do you really not remember?

319
00:27:32,940 --> 00:27:34,280
Huh?

320
00:27:35,800 --> 00:27:37,300
Donoko.

321
00:27:39,300 --> 00:27:41,300
Donoko…?

322
00:27:43,300 --> 00:27:45,420
Ah, Saruhashi?

323
00:27:46,780 --> 00:27:54,800
We... Me, you, and Hin—
the six people blacked out in the album—are...

324
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:01,300
Donoko…

325
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:08,480
I’m Sonoko Saruhashi
from Shukan Apollo.

326
00:28:08,480 --> 00:28:14,200
Kanta Sakurai...
and you were here too.

327
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:17,180
Sho Takaki.

328
00:28:18,420 --> 00:28:20,000
Why are you here?

329
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:23,480
I’m here for an interview.

330
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:27,940
I’d like to ask you a few questions,
if that’s okay.

331
00:28:27,940 --> 00:28:28,800
Huh?

332
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:35,220
You were friends with Toshiki Takeda,
who passed away last night, right?

333
00:28:35,220 --> 00:28:37,180
What’s happening, Saruhashi?

334
00:28:37,180 --> 00:28:42,300
Takaki, Sakurai, and the late Takeda.

335
00:28:42,300 --> 00:28:47,060
Also Emi Nakajima,
Takahiro Koyama, and Taisuke Haryu.

336
00:28:47,060 --> 00:28:52,740
Why are the photos of these people
blacked out in the album?

337
00:28:52,740 --> 00:28:56,800
Do you see any
commonalities or connection?

338
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:03,460
We’re just a close friends, you know?

339
00:29:03,460 --> 00:29:04,800
Right?

340
00:29:09,020 --> 00:29:11,460
That’s really all there is?

341
00:29:11,460 --> 00:29:13,500
That’s what I’m saying.

342
00:29:14,860 --> 00:29:17,300
Though it seems he feels differently.

343
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:21,940
Takaki.

344
00:29:23,180 --> 00:29:28,940
You just called me
“Donoko” earlier, didn’t you?

345
00:29:30,160 --> 00:29:33,300
So, you actually remember…

346
00:29:35,340 --> 00:29:39,800
…bullying me?

347
00:29:44,720 --> 00:29:47,800
I remember it well.

348
00:29:47,800 --> 00:29:51,780
I’ve never forgotten it.

349
00:29:54,560 --> 00:29:57,620
Because of that, I still
have claustrophobia.

350
00:29:57,620 --> 00:30:02,040
I can’t even use elevators,
which is really inconvenient.

351
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:04,560
That’s ancient history… now?

352
00:30:04,560 --> 00:30:05,800
Now?

353
00:30:07,500 --> 00:30:14,980
As kids, you were bullies… and now
you’ve grown up, working, married, raising kids…

354
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:23,800
acting like you’ve always been good.
And now, you’re saying we shouldn’t talk about the past?

355
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:34,800
Those who were bullied can never forget.

356
00:30:38,980 --> 00:30:42,000
- That’s why…
- Huh?

357
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:49,020
So... you killed him?

358
00:30:49,020 --> 00:30:52,300
- Hey, Takaki!
- Did you take revenge?

359
00:30:55,800 --> 00:30:57,800
That’s how you start?

360
00:31:02,800 --> 00:31:07,020
I’m relieved.
This makes my work worthwhile.

361
00:31:07,020 --> 00:31:12,680
I plan to publish an article eventually,
so if you remember anything, please contact me.

362
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:30,700
“Shukan Apollo
Sonoko Saruhashi”

363
00:31:45,980 --> 00:31:48,440
Go for it, King!

364
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:50,480
Die!

365
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:53,100
That was close!

366
00:31:53,100 --> 00:31:54,520
Damn it!

367
00:32:04,700 --> 00:32:08,000
What’s wrong, Hin?

368
00:32:09,520 --> 00:32:12,620
I hear something...

369
00:32:12,620 --> 00:32:14,120
Huh?

370
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:17,380
Help me!

371
00:32:19,620 --> 00:32:24,360
That voice is Saruhashi,
the transfer student.

372
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:27,620
You know, Niko's...

373
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:32,120
Someone! Please open this!

374
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,120
Stop it!

375
00:33:00,120 --> 00:33:02,620
Hey!

376
00:33:02,620 --> 00:33:05,620
Who's inside there?

377
00:33:05,620 --> 00:33:09,120
Who's inside there?

378
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:13,120
Who's inside there?

379
00:33:14,120 --> 00:33:16,620
Alright, let’s go. Okay.

380
00:33:16,620 --> 00:33:19,120
Ah, that’s good, yeah, yeah...

381
00:33:19,120 --> 00:33:22,120
Alright, here we go.
Ready, set, go.

382
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:24,620
Ah, wonderful!
So cute. Yes.

383
00:33:24,620 --> 00:33:27,120
Alright, let’s do this.

384
00:33:27,120 --> 00:33:29,120
3, 2, 1, go.

385
00:33:58,660 --> 00:34:00,620
Help me!

386
00:34:15,740 --> 00:34:18,120
Stop it!

387
00:34:18,120 --> 00:34:21,620
Who's inside there?

388
00:34:21,620 --> 00:34:24,340
Who's inside there?

389
00:34:24,340 --> 00:34:25,620
Stop it!

390
00:34:25,620 --> 00:34:28,620
Who's inside there?

391
00:34:28,620 --> 00:34:31,000
Who's inside there?

392
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:33,620
Help me!

393
00:34:33,620 --> 00:34:37,120
Stop! Stop!

394
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:38,940
Who's inside there?

395
00:34:38,940 --> 00:34:41,880
Help! Open up!

396
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:43,520
Stop it!

397
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:46,740
Help! Help!

398
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:49,540
Yes, alright.

399
00:34:49,540 --> 00:34:52,120
Let’s continue as is, okay.

400
00:34:52,120 --> 00:34:55,120
Yes, yes... come on, smile.

401
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:56,620
More, more.

402
00:34:56,620 --> 00:34:59,620
Alright, give me a smile.
Yes, yes, yes... that’s good.

403
00:34:59,620 --> 00:35:01,620
More smile please.

404
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:07,520
- Good work.
- Good work.

405
00:35:07,520 --> 00:35:10,120
So, how was the surprise interview?

406
00:35:10,120 --> 00:35:12,680
Hmm... it was okay...

407
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:22,540
Still, it’s ironic that a kid whose dream was to
fly in the sky ended up falling to their death.

408
00:35:24,980 --> 00:35:27,060
Flying in the sky?

409
00:35:28,340 --> 00:35:29,620
What?

410
00:35:33,560 --> 00:35:35,020
Thanks.

411
00:35:35,020 --> 00:35:38,020
We both work, so
this much is nothing.

412
00:35:38,020 --> 00:35:39,620
As expected of King.

413
00:35:39,620 --> 00:35:41,200
Kanon, don’t call me that.

414
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:44,880
That actually fits.
Dad’s the king of this house.

415
00:35:44,880 --> 00:35:47,380
He’s protecting us...
Right?

416
00:35:47,380 --> 00:35:50,200
- Right, King?
- Stop calling me King at home.

417
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:53,920
Kanon, how was art class today?

418
00:35:53,920 --> 00:35:57,300
- It was fun.
- What did you use the plastic bottle for?

419
00:35:57,300 --> 00:35:59,520
We peeled off the label and...

420
00:35:59,520 --> 00:36:01,620
- Good job.
- Good job.

421
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:27,000
I never thought
you’d actually contact me.

422
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:31,000
So, what is it?
You said you wanted to talk.

423
00:36:35,200 --> 00:36:37,500
I’ve never forgotten…

424
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:45,420
That we... bullied you.

425
00:36:48,640 --> 00:36:55,980
They were childhood memories,
and it wasn’t meant seriously,

426
00:36:55,980 --> 00:37:00,080
but I remember we did it just for fun.

427
00:37:03,100 --> 00:37:09,000
Honestly, we knew you hated it.

428
00:37:11,700 --> 00:37:19,360
But... if you want to take revenge like that,
I can’t understand it.

429
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:24,300
Don’t go after those guys.

430
00:37:25,380 --> 00:37:28,000
If you want, do it to me.

431
00:37:32,620 --> 00:37:38,180
Did you call me here
just to say that?

432
00:37:38,180 --> 00:37:41,360
Seriously stupid...
really pointless.

433
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:43,640
- Oh no, a fire!
- Huh, there’s fire!

434
00:37:43,640 --> 00:37:46,520
Look, look, look... see!

435
00:37:46,520 --> 00:37:48,000
It’s burning, see.

436
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:50,500
- It’s burning.
- Eh!

437
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:11,420
Kantaro...

438
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:35,000
What are you doing?
That’s dangerous, hey!

439
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:42,000
Fire! Fire!

440
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:44,500
Please evacuate immediately.

441
00:39:26,020 --> 00:39:29,500
It’s okay... it’s okay...

442
00:39:33,980 --> 00:39:36,000
It’s okay...

443
00:39:42,420 --> 00:39:45,000
Who's inside there?

444
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:48,000
Who's inside there?

445
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:50,860
Who's inside there?

446
00:39:50,860 --> 00:39:52,340
Stop it!

447
00:39:52,340 --> 00:39:55,000
Who's inside there?

448
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:58,760
Stop! Help!

449
00:39:58,760 --> 00:40:00,500
Help!

450
00:40:00,500 --> 00:40:02,500
Who's inside there?

451
00:40:02,500 --> 00:40:05,000
Who's inside there?

452
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:07,940
Who's inside there?

453
00:40:07,940 --> 00:40:10,000
Stop it!

454
00:40:11,500 --> 00:40:14,600
Help... someone...

455
00:40:19,420 --> 00:40:22,000
What the hell are you doing, idiot!

456
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:25,740
- Are you okay?
- Thank you…

457
00:40:25,740 --> 00:40:27,500
This way.

458
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:46,400
Alright, I’m getting you down.

459
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:48,900
Mr. Sakurai, do you understand?

460
00:40:48,900 --> 00:40:51,400
You’ve arrived at the hospital.

461
00:41:16,060 --> 00:41:20,900
Why’d you go and do
something so reckless?

462
00:41:25,400 --> 00:41:27,400
Because it was murder.

463
00:41:31,100 --> 00:41:34,080
How can you say that
with such confidence?

464
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:42,900
Takeda drew a picture of flying in the sky
and died from a fall.

465
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:49,900
Sakurai drew a picture of a firefighter.

466
00:41:51,780 --> 00:41:58,260
So the moment I saw the fire,
I thought this was a planned murder.

467
00:41:58,260 --> 00:42:00,020
No way.

468
00:42:01,680 --> 00:42:07,900
Besides... if any more of you die,
that would be a problem.

469
00:42:12,260 --> 00:42:14,400
What’s that supposed to mean?

470
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:21,400
When Takeda died...

471
00:42:26,060 --> 00:42:27,900
I thought...

472
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:35,400
Good. Serves them right.

473
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:46,400
But if someone is happy when
someone dies, then that means…

474
00:42:49,340 --> 00:42:51,900
It makes me look like the bad kid.

475
00:43:01,420 --> 00:43:08,900
I’ve worked hard because
I never wanted to be a bad kid like you.

476
00:43:11,060 --> 00:43:13,260
Worked hard...

477
00:43:13,260 --> 00:43:14,900
worked hard... worked hard...

478
00:43:17,780 --> 00:43:20,400
I changed my own life.

479
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:27,900
You’ll never understand.

480
00:43:34,120 --> 00:43:36,060
What kind of...

481
00:43:38,560 --> 00:43:40,900
Hardships I’ve endured.

482
00:43:47,800 --> 00:43:49,900
I won’t forgive.

483
00:43:54,520 --> 00:44:02,400
Those of you who bullied me and
the person behind this incident exploiting my bullying...

484
00:44:04,360 --> 00:44:06,400
I will never forgive.

485
00:44:23,560 --> 00:44:25,100
Takaki.

486
00:44:32,900 --> 00:44:35,400
Shall we end this together?
